version_description: This is the only version. I created it because there wasn't one. It's a great song.
Electric classic guitar with chorus and a little reverb,from verse 3 onward add a little distortion to the effects.alternatively can be played simply on acoustic guitar.

song_name: All The World Is A Stage
And Now The Waltz Cest La Vie
version_description: Slade comeback single from 1981,which signalled a Slade 80s revival,play with Electric Guitar just Chorus/Reverb on verses adding Fuzz post gain slightly down for Intro and Bridges.

song_name: Auld Langs Syne Youll Never Walk Alone
version_description: Verse 1,chorus 1 played slowly,single strum or finger picked.Bridge play faster and more rock style electric with overdrive,Verse 2,Chorus 2 onwards faster again to end.https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TTPl9CrRkB4.

This version includes correct chord sequence Am A7sus4 D,it is complete and sounds better using open 5 chords and has the open B,this tab is then easy to play on accoustic as well as electric using open chords.

song_name: Did Ya Mama Ever Tell Ya

version_description: A song written about Sir Bob Geldof by Slade to celebrate Live Aid,very simple to play using electric guitar with overdrive/harmony effects,use gain boost on the Outro lead guitar.
I made the change to let it sound better and make it easier to play. Enjoy.

song_name: Get Down And Get With It

version_description: Played with Capo on 2,the Gadd9 chord can be dropped but i think it adds to the flavour,Electric guitar classic fuzz/chorus effects,but equally sounds good using the strum pattern on acoustic guitar.
Song from 1977 Play with Electric Guitar Fuzz/Overdrive effects.
Recorded as a track for the Crackers album 1985 Unfortunately no video link for just this track.
